In the past hours other associations have instead launched the alarm on the situation of people living on the street, denouncing forced clearances of the most precarious such as homeless, migrants in the fields and workers of sex in view of the Games, as well as expulsions and harassments suffered. The activists have "seen" several statues with cartels hanging to vehicular of the messages on the "social cleansing as inheritance", which leaves "a thousand children in the middle of the road". The initiative was organized by a collective of about 80 associations and NGOs called 'Revers de la mèdaille' ('Rovescio della Medal'). In front of the Senate, they then gave the symbolic way to "a first race" of the Olympics, launching boe that represent the Olympic rings in the pool of the Luxembourg Gardens and colored smokers against the "palms of the Olympics".
Four months from Paris 2024, activists reported that in Paris, "3,500 people sleep on the ice and a thousand in the gyms", underlining that "it is necessary to take care of them so that the Games are dignified and beautiful for all". To conclude, in Dugny (Seine-Saint-Denis), in front of the Media Village of the Olympic Games that will be inaugurated in the coming days, a seventy of activists for environmental and housing rights (Dal) protested against the fragmentation and cementification of the areas around the Olympic sites, on appeal of the collective Youth for Climate.&nbsp;
