AGI -&nbsp;Great Festival for Hindus in India, Nepal, in other countries of southern Asia and in the diaspora: with the festival Holi welcome the spring covering of colored powder>. Media and social relaunch photographs and videos of the celebrants who rejoice by launching each other colored powders on the street, with dances, music, prayers and sharing special foods. Holi is seen as a moment to welcome the good that defeats evil, to let go of the negative, to mean a moment of rebirth and rejuvenation. As usual, it coincides with the last full moon day of the lunar month.
&nbsp;
Holi is based on the Hindu legend of Holika, a female demon who tries to kill his nephew Prahlad because he loves the Hindu god Vishnu. But Prahlad miraculously survives the burning fire while Holika is consumed by flames. Within the celebrations, the evening before Holi, there are falos in the belief that they will destroy evil > to make good triumph. Among the many commemorative curiosities, there is the Holika Dahan in a village near Gandhinagar, the capital of Gujarat, which has been carrying out a tradition for 700 years. A 30-metre circumference brazier that uses 200 tons of wood gives rise to flames more than 10 meters high. It is one of the most celebrated celebrations in India, which is why millions of people reach cities and villages of origin on the days preceding the day of celebration and processions take place at the four corners of the country.
